d 'XTBFKBREAK': module to estimate common structural breaks in heterogeneous panels with correlated common effects and (optionally) endogenous regressors
d
d	xtbfkbreak estimates a heterogeneous panel-data model whose
d slope coefficients undergo one or more common structural breaks
d at	unknown dates, while cross-sectional dependence is
d generated by an unobserved multifactor error structure.  It
d brings the two    papers of Baltagi, Feng and Kao into a single
d command:	  (2016) Baltagi, Feng & Kao marry Pesaran's (2006)
d Common Correlated Effects (CCE) estimator to Bai's (1997, 2010)  
d	   least-squares change-point estimation.  Unobserved
d factors are partialled out with the cross-section averages of    
d	 depvar and the regressors; the common break date(s) are
d then estimated consistently by least squares, and the regime	   
d	slopes by CCE mean group.  A key result is that the panel
d pins down the break date itself (super-consistency), not	   
d   merely the break fraction.	      (2019) Baltagi, Feng & Kao
d extend this to endogenous regressors.  A second endogeneity
d channel, Cov(eps,v)!=0, is allowed		on top of the
d factor-induced correlation, and a break in the error-factor
d loadings is permitted.  The break date is	       still
d estimated by OLS (which stays consistent under endogeneity,
d Perron & Yamamoto 2015), and the regime slopes by	      
d CCE-IV / 2SLS mean group.  Because CCE wipes out the factors
d instead of estimating them, a break in the factor	      
d loadings needs no special treatment.	  Give instruments in the
d (endog = instruments) list to obtain the endogenous-regressor
d (2019) estimator; omit it for the    exogenous (2016) estimator. 
d Use nocce to drop the factor structure entirely (the papers'
d "Model 1").  For the algebra, see    {help
d xtbfkbreak_methods:xtbfkbreak methods}. 
d
d KW: panel data
d KW: structural breaks
d KW: common correlated effects
d KW: endogeneity
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260711
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f xtbfkbreak.ado
f xtbfkbreak.sthlp
f xtbfkbreak_methods.sthlp
f xtbfkbreak_example.do
